'''Elan Sel'Sabagno''', also known as '''Elan Sleazebaggano''', was a [[Gender|male]] [[Balosar (species)|Balosar]] [[death stick]] dealer on the [[planet]] [[Coruscant]] during the [[Separatist Crisis]]. A chance encounter with [[Jedi Knight]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and his [[mind trick]]s resulted in Sel'Sabagno deciding to take up a more honest life.

==Biography==
Elan Sel'Sabagno<ref name="Coruscant">{{EncyclopediaCite|Coruscant}}</ref> was a [[Gender|male]] [[Balosar (species)|Balosar]]<ref name="DB" /> who was active on [[Coruscant]], the [[capital]] of the [[Galactic Republic]], during the [[Separatist Crisis]].<ref name="Episode II" /> A small-time criminal,<ref name="Want to be Jedi">[[Star Wars: I Want to Be a Jedi (2017)|''Star Wars: I Want to Be a Jedi'' (2017)]]</ref> Sel'Sabagno made [[Currency|money]]<ref name="Episode II" /> as a [[slythmonger]],<ref name="CL 2016">[[Star Wars: Complete Locations (2016)|''Star Wars: Complete Locations'']]</ref> tending to tour Coruscant's nightclubs to sell his addictive [[death stick]]s.<ref name="SW:TVE">''[[Star Wars: The Visual Encyclopedia]]''</ref> In [[22 BBY]], shortly before the [[First Battle of Geonosis|outbreak]] of the [[Clone Wars]], Sel'Sabagno was present in the [[Outlander Club]] and attempted to sell his [[death]] sticks in the drinks bar to [[Jedi Knight]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi]], who was [[Plot to assassinate Senator Amidala|searching]] for the [[Clawdite]] [[bounty hunter]] [[Zam Wesell]]. Kenobi used a [[mind trick]] to convince Sel'Sabagno that he did not want to sell the [[Jedi]] any death sticks and instead wanted to go home and rethink his life.<ref name="Episode II" /> Later that year,<ref name="Date">''[[Star Wars: Timelines]]'' dates the events of ''Brotherhood'' to [[22 BBY]].</ref> while in a [[Unidentified pub|pub]] in the city [[Zarra]], Kenobi recalled the incident, noting that the last time he was in a bar, he had nudged a criminal to rethink his life.<ref name="Brotherhood">[[Brotherhood (novel)|''Brotherhood'']]</ref>

Kenobi's mind trick convinced Sel'Sabagno to begin living an honest life for himself.<ref name="Want to be Jedi" /> By the time Kenobi and his [[Padawan]] [[Anakin Skywalker]] were assisting Wesell at the back of the establishment, Sel'Sabagno had already left the club.<ref name="CL 2016" /> In the [[Imperial Era]],<ref name="The Right Wrong Turn">[[Star Wars Adventures (2017) 25|''Star Wars Adventures'' (2017) 25]]</ref> Sel'Sabagno,<ref name="Elan Confirmed">{{Twitter|DelilahSDawson|status/1406643019022049280|[[Delilah S. Dawson]]|date=2021-06-20|quote=I feel like this might be my greatest canon win-- proof that Elan Sleazebaggano really did turn his life around, perfectly captured by @m_saltel.|archivedate=20210620162148|archivefile=File:DelilahSDawson-ElanSleazebagganoDad-Twitter.png}} {{C|In response to: [Images of Elan Sleazebaggano] Happy Father's Day to the best Dad in the galaxy 👍}}</ref> by then with a child of his own, passed by a conversation between [[Leia Skywalker Organa Solo|Leia Organa]] and [[Forzaa]] on Coruscant.<ref name="The Right Wrong Turn" />

==Personality and traits==
[[File:ElanSleazebaggano-ALTA.png|thumb|180px|right|Sel'Sabagno could curl his [[antennapalps]] to conceal them under his hair.]]
Always searching for [[Galactic Credit Standard|credits]], Elan Sel'Sabagno made his living selling death sticks to patrons of the Outlander Club and other hot spots in the underlevels of Coruscant, targeting both desperate addicts and unwise thrill-seekers.<ref name="DB" /> However, Sel'Sabagno was weak-minded, as Obi-Wan Kenobi performed a mind trick on him and convinced him to not sell death sticks to the Jedi Knight and to go home to rethink his life,<ref name="Episode II" /> with Sel'Sabagno deciding to take up an honest life. This decision stuck, resulting Elan eventually becoming a family man.<ref name="Want to be Jedi" />

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|Elan Sleazebaggano was altered in postproduction, too late for toys in the works to change. The proper Elan has no ears. Reference photography didn't have this digital alteration. Toys had a running change to remove his ears.|[[Pablo Hidalgo]]|<ref name="Hidalgo tweet #2">{{Twitter|pablohidalgo|status/981652528931549186|[[Pablo Hidalgo]]|quote=Today's Star Wars Show reminds me: Elan Sleazebaggano was altered in postproduction, too late for toys in the works to change. The proper Elan has no ears. Reference photography didn't have this digital alteration. Toys had a running change to remove his ears.|archivefile=File:HidalgoSleazebaggano.png}}</ref>}}
Elan Sel'Sabagno was portrayed by [[Matt Doran]] in the [[2002]] film [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']].<ref name="Episode II" /> The character was named by ''[[Star Wars]]'' creator [[George Lucas]].<ref name="Hidalgo tweet #1">{{Twitter|pablohidalgo|status/981665660496302080|[[Pablo Hidalgo]]|quote=George Lucas did.|archivefile=File:HidalgoSleazebaggano.png}} {{C|in response to "''I just wanna know who it was that came up with that ''[Elan Sleazebaggano's]'' name.''"}}</ref> In [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]], the character was first identified as [[Elan Sel'Sabagno/Legends|Elan Sel'Sabagno]],<ref name="GPB-SWG10">{{GamerCite|10|Galactic Power Brokers}}</ref> a name that was canonized by the [[Coruscant (reference book)|Coruscant encyclopedia]].<ref name="Coruscant" /> His alternative last name, Sleazebaggano, was canonized by the [[Databank (2014-)|StarWars.com Databank]].<ref name="DB" />

Although Sel'Sabagno's [[ear]]s were replaced by [[antennapalps]] in post-production of ''Attack of the Clones'', the reference photography didn't have the digital alteration, causing early Sleazebaggano toys to have ears instead of antennapalps.<ref name="Hidalgo tweet #2" /> Sel'Sabagno later made a cameo in the background of the [[2019]] comic [[Star Wars Adventures (2017) 25|''Star Wars Adventures'' (2017) 25]] by [[Delilah S. Dawson]],<ref name="The Right Wrong Turn" /> who confirmed the character featured was indeed Sel'Sabagno via Twitter. Dawson considered his cameo among her greatest contributions to the ''[[Star Wars]]'' galaxy as it confirmed he had, indeed, turned his life around. Dawson also thanked artist [[Margaux Saltel]] for capturing the moment in what she believed was a perfect manner.<ref name="Elan Confirmed" />

